M.G.L. c. 186, \u00a7 14.proposition: Under M.G.L. c. 186, § 14, every residential lease in Massachusetts includes an implied covenant of quiet enjoyment, guaranteeing the tenant's right to undisturbed possession and enjoyment of their rental premises.

M.G.L. c. 212, \u00a7 3.proposition: This Court has jurisdiction over this matter under M.G.L. c. 212, § 3, as the amount in controversy does not exceed $25,000, and this is a civil action arising under Massachusetts law.
